row.cell:
1869, 1,728,000; 1874, 4,700,000; 1884, increasing; 1885,
                                        no change, countless numbers: 1887, still on the increase;
                                        1888, no change

frus:attachment.p:
“During the year quite a number of vessels have raided Alaskan waters
                                for seals and other fur-bearing animals.” (H. R. Ex. Doc. No. 153,
                                49th Cong., 1st sess., vol. 32.)
